<br>
-how to pull the lair and some simple fight strategies on handling 5+ giants.<br>
-showed those present how to do simple CR from out of her lair if you fail on Vox.  <br>
-buffing strategy.  Buffing strategy is absolutely critical vs Vox and Nagafen, if not done properly it can mean the difference between success or failure.  And no its not as simple as casting your standard buffs with magic resist and cold resist.  You must cast them in a certain order for maximum effect.<br>
-how to check if Vox is agro without running into her lair and finding out the hard way.  <br>
<br>
Well maybe some other time we can make another go at this when there's enough interest and there's not another conflicting open raid going on.  Seems like most people can't remember the last time Vox was killed on zeb server.  You know how many RBBs, Eye patches, and White Scales are going to waste?  I heard that a lot of people are gun shy of Vox now after so many failures on her partly because of the difficult CR if the raid fails.  Well CR is a SNAP if you know how to do it right, it just takes some knowledge of the game and you don't need monks, rogues, or necros to bail you out.  <br>
<br>
I know that Vox raids is kinda like College football.  You get 4-5 levels of eligibility then you don't qualify and have to move on.  Those with the most in game experience can't raid anymore and have to move on to the bigger uber mobs.  Meanwhile you have newer blood that don't know what they're doing and must be shown the ropes.  However if a raid isn't done for a prolonged period of time then you don't have any raid veterans to show the newer guys because there's a lot of lvl 52 characters that have never been on any vox or nag raids.  <br>
<br>
I could be wrong but I think the nature of the 52+ level limit on Vox and Nag means that they will most likely be multi guild/public raids for the most part.  Most guilds probably don't have the core of their people between 46-52.  <br>
<br>
So anyways next time you guys want to make a serious attempt at her let me know and I'll be glad to help out. <p>----------------------- <BR>
Zartuul the Tactician <BR>
Grave Lord, Zeb <BR>
