<br>
I estimate that doing CR after a failed Vox run can take less then half an hour.  If you have just two people that know what they're doing you can have everyones body out of her lair WHEN SHE IS STILL UP in under 10 mins.  So you just have healer/caster types bind near the goblin king room and they CR the melee types, then you buff up and try again.<br>
<br>
With practice you will learn what works and what doesn't work.  With each failed vox run you become that much closer to doing it right and since I can guarantee you failure won't be that big of a deal you really have nothing to be afraid of in trying this raid until you succeed.  <br>
<br>
My personal most hated raid in its time was the dragon Hoshkar in Veeshan's Peak.  I think I was in over a dozen attempts on him before he finally died for my first time.  Each failure meant about 2.5 to 3 hours of CR and rebuff time before we could try again.  The fight typically took between 40 seconds to a minute and a half depending how fast we all died.  We just kept beating our heads against the wall no matter how much it hurt until we finally won.  That's what you have to do to get over Vox.  Once you know how to do Vox AND you have the proper resist gear she is EASY and you can reap the fruits of your work time and time again because right now nobody is doing it.<br>
<br>
Experienced lvl 50 Vox veterans can kill her with a mere 30 people easily.  It's all in the technique, strategy, and equipment.  Once you have that you're set.  With newer people I would personally want around 48 there. <p>----------------------- <BR>
