</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uaxterixenobelix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Axterix EnObelix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grumpy Ol' Gnome</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#333333>(9/14/01 2:02:37 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vox debriefing</span><hr size=1> &gt;&gt;Experienced lvl 50 Vox veterans can kill her with a mere 30 people easily. It's all in the technique, strategy, and equipment. Once you have that you're set. With newer people I would personally want around 48 there. <br>
<br>
With the right group mix, I'm positive 18 could do it.  My own goal at one time was to do it with 12 and a few high level buffers (which I'm sure is doable for Naggy, but probably not for Vox, though I think we could get pretty close).<br>
<br>
The experience and gear factors are huge.  <br>
<br>
My advice for tanks (and everyone else, really) that want to fight Vox... get an insta-cast junk buff item.  One of the high level coldain rings (8, 9, or 10).  A gobby earring.  Or if you can't get either of those, hook up with a tinkerer and get an aqualung (50 charges of breath of the dead, works from inventory, sells back to vendor for about 200 plat, probably cost 3-400 plat to buy from a tinkerer).  For tanks, it just means after every time that Vox breathes and dispels a buff, you click and put a buff back up.  You keep your hp, resist, haste,  stat, and ac buffs.  End result: you need less healing, are healed more effeciently, and do more damage.  You also don't need the normal 4 junk buffs, 2 will do, allowing for more useful buffs.<br>
<br>
For casters, an item like bracer of the hidden works well too, as casters don't have to worry about having to shift off target as much... and you can take a second to slap the clerics with it (just be sure to coordinate with the cleric before-hand, make sure it is his #1 junk-buff, etc).<br>
<br>
The basic redo junk buff idea is something as an enchanter I've been doing on Vox raids for ages... I used the recycle time on mana seive to cast haze on myself, the level 4 enchanter ac buff... cheap mana cost, low casting time, fit in just about perfectly.  End result, when combined with berserker spirit, I'd lose a bubble or less of health.  I'm sure other casters have cheap spells, fast casting, that they could use.  Of course, it works best for enchanters, as their role in the actual Vox fight is to seive, which they can do at max range, and it has a recycle time to use as they see fit. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uaxterixenobelix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Axterix EnObelix</A> at: 9/14/01 2:09:06 pm<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm4.showMessage?topicID=132.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm4.showMessage?topicID=128.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm4.emailToFriend?topicID=130.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm4.threadControl?topicID=130.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm4.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=130.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm4.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=130.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email no